The paper deals with quantum information theory, specifically with quantum error-correcting codes and unitary designs. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.QI (Quantum Physics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of commutative subgroups and automorphisms, which are related to algebraic structures, making cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Clifford gates, which are important in quantum computing, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category.
